subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks.
Anthaxia ( A. ) ephippiata
was described by
Redtenbacher ( 1850 )
from a single female specimen (
Figs. 9–10
), apparently collected by Kotschy in the Fars province, during his expedition to Persia (
Edmondson & Lack 2006
).

The deposition of the holotype of this species indicated in recent catalogues (
Bílý 1997
;
Bellamy 2008
) seems to be incorrect, as it has not been found in the HNHM ( O . Merkl, pers. comm.).
